# Responsive Design Skills

## Overview
Patterns and techniques for building interfaces that adapt gracefully across devices and contexts.

## Breakpoint System

### Standard Breakpoints
```css
--breakpoint-sm: 640px;  /* Mobile landscape */
--breakpoint-md: 768px;  /* Tablet */
--breakpoint-lg: 1024px; /* Desktop */
--breakpoint-xl: 1280px; /* Wide desktop */
--breakpoint-2xl: 1536px; /* Ultra-wide */
```

### Mobile-First Workflow
```tsx
// Start with mobile styles, add overrides for larger
function Card() {
  return (
    <div className="
      p-4                    /* Mobile: 16px */
      md:p-6                 /* Tablet: 24px */
      lg:p-8                 /* Desktop: 32px */
    ">
      {/* Content */}
    </div>
  )
}
```

## Common Responsive Patterns

### 1. Fluid Typography
Scale text based on viewport, with clamps.

```css
/* clamp(min, preferred, max) */
font-size: clamp(1rem, 2.5vw + 0.5rem, 2rem);
```

### 2. Container Queries
Style based on element width, not viewport.

```css
@container (min-width: 400px) {
  .card-content {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
  }
}
```

### 3. Aspect Ratio Boxes
Reserve space for media to prevent CLS.

```tsx
<div className="aspect-video relative">
  <Image 
    src="/hero.jpg" 
    fill 
    alt="Hero" 
    sizes="100vw"
  />
</div>
```

### 4. Responsive Grid
```css
.grid {
  display: grid;
  gap: 1rem;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr;
}

@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
}

@media (min-width: 1024px) {
  .grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); }
}
```

### 5. Hide/Show Patterns
```tsx
// Mobile-only
<div className="block md:hidden" />

// Desktop-only  
<div className="hidden md:block" />

// Tablet and up
<div className="hidden sm:block" />
```

## Touch-Friendly Targets
- Minimum touch target: 44×44px (iOS HIG)
- Spacing between targets: 8px minimum
- Avoid hover-only interactions on mobile

## Testing Checklist
- [ ] Mobile (375px)
- [ ] Mobile landscape (667px)
- [ ] Tablet (768px)
- [ ] Tablet landscape (1024px)
- [ ] Desktop (1280px)
- [ ] Large desktop (1536px)
- [ ] Touch interactions work on mobile
- [ ] No horizontal scroll at any size

## Skills Integration
- Use with design-system.skills for token-driven responsive values
- Combine with performance.skills for responsive images
- Apply accessibility.skills for screen reader consideration
